Reasoning: The paper discusses similarity datasets in linguistics and psychology, which are both relevant to the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed approach of using commonality lists instead of numerical similarity scores is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves developing models for meaning representation. The evaluation procedure suggested in the paper also involves using the structure of human judgments, which could be relevant to the field of computational cognition (cs.CC). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) as it discusses methods for evaluating the similarity of words, phrases, and sentences.
